		<li id="comment_135037">
			
			<!-- Moderation? -->
			
			<p>You can probably use a 1.8 to 2.5 adapter (and optional 2.5 to 3.5 adapter) plus a USB or FireWire enclosure to test and format, but I don&#8217;t believe this offers the same depth of testing as native IDE.  If it&#8217;s your only option, though, it may well suffice.</p>
<p>The nice thing about the 1.8&#8243; drives is that they are interface-compatible with larger drives, but on a smaller scale.  The same tests and formats can be applied as with larger drives.</p>
			
			<div class="meta">
				<div class="left">
					<strong><cite><a href='http://www.command-tab.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Collin</a></cite></strong>
				</div>
				<div class="right">
					<small>
						<a href="#comment_135037" title="Permanent link to this comment">
							March 3rd, 2008 at 11:39 AM						</a> 					</small>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
			</div>

		</li>

	
	
