		<li class="alt" id="comment_145063">
			
			<!-- Moderation? -->
			
			<p>I know this is about a year and a half later, but I dropped my ipod in water and found that you can open it up with a guitar pick and you don&#8217;t need fancy tools. Also, there are little tabs that you flip up so you don&#8217;t have to just pull the ribbons out, so look out for those- The ones for the battery are brown, and the one for the hard drive is black and you&#8217;ll see it where the orange ribbon connects. To open it, just put your fingernail under the opposite side of the black tab and pull up towards you and it&#8217;ll pop up, allowing you to remove the ribbon easily and without wiggling back and forth, which is dangerous.</p>
<p>Dearon</p>
			
			<div class="meta">
				<div class="left">
