			<p>Werner, the drive that Apple uses is a Samsung MFG SKU  HS161JQ.  The drive is an 8mm and will not fit with you 80G or 120GB back panel.  The 160GB I listed is less expensive than the Toshiba.  In order to make it work you will need a thinker back panel to handle the additional room.  If you are doing that, you will also be able to install a stronger battery that lasts longer.  <br />
