		<li id="comment_145848">
			
			<!-- Moderation? -->
			
			<p>Harrier</p>
<p>I think Toshiba MK1011GAH is not 5mm. It is 8mm.<br />
Perhaps, The last letter &#8220;H&#8221; of &#8220;MKXXXXGAH&#8221; means High, that is 8mm.<br />
On the other hand, &#8220;L&#8221; means Low, that is 5mm.<br />
The largest model which can be installed into iPod 5.5G is MK8025GAL (and MK8022GAA) at this moment.<br />
MK8022GAA has a firmware specialized to iPod only, but MK8025GAL can be used not only iPod but also PC or other machine, I suppose.  </p>
<p>By the way, after I gave up installing MK1231GAL (120GB, 5mm) into my iPod 5.5G, I ordered MK2341GAL (240GB, 8mm) and back panel from Rapid Repair and waiting for shipping now.</p>
			
			<div class="meta">
				<div class="left">
					<strong><cite>Piejesu</cite></strong>
				</div>
				<div class="right">
					<small>
						<a href="#comment_145848" title="Permanent link to this comment">
							February 12th, 2009 at 3:02 PM						</a> 					</small>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
			</div>

		</li>

	
	
