		<li id="comment_146021">
			
			<!-- Moderation? -->
			
			<p>We perform the upgrades frequently for the 5 and 5.5G iPODs, as well as, repairs for the same models, including all the other previous generations.  We also repair and upgrade the 6G Video.<br />
Using Compact Flash memory in the iPODs is another upgrade option we offer, however, the cost differential needs to be considered with this option.  Of course capacity is limited in todays CF market as well.  The single point of failure of the mechanical drive is removed with an increase in seek/read times and significantly less drain on the battery.  WE have had good success with the HS series drives in the iPODs, with similar observations as noted here by Johannes.</p>
			
			<div class="meta">
				<div class="left">
					<strong><cite>MiPODrepair</cite></strong>
				</div>
