		<li class="alt" id="comment_147170">
			
			<!-- Moderation? -->
			
			<p>Just completed an upgrade of the slim version (30GB iPOD Video) to Samsung&#8217;s 80GB HS082HB.  Ran in to a hitch and it took a LOT longer than I expected but it&#8217;s all up and running now.</p>
<p>Problem was that, unlike everything mentioned so far, my iPOD came stock with a Hitachi drive, not a Toshiba.  While the Toshiba (and my new Samsung) use a ZIF HDD connector ribbon that is .25mm thick, the Hitachi uses one that has a thicker .35mm end going in to the HDD.  When I found that this connector simply would not fit into my Samsung HS082HB I did a little research and came up with exactly one online store (<a href="http://store.ifixipodsfast.com/" rel="nofollow">http://store.ifixipodsfast.com/</a>) which seemed aware of the difference and would sell you either the thick (hitachi) or thin (samsung) type.</p>
<p>No way I wanted to wait several more days, however, so I spent an hour or two with an exacto knife shaving that .35mm down to .25mm.  It wasn&#8217;t easy (and didn&#8217;t work the first try) but eventually I got it and now I&#8217;m listening to tunes of my 80GB with upgraded 580mAh battery.</p>
<p>If anyone is still updating the main article, it might be worth mentioning the Hitachi-style .35mm thick ZIF connector.</p>
			
			<div class="meta">
				<div class="left">
					<strong><cite>Owen</cite></strong>
				</div>
				<div class="right">
					<small>
						<a href="#comment_147170" title="Permanent link to this comment">
							August 20th, 2009 at 9:38 PM						</a> 					</small>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
			</div>

		</li>

	
	
